						               													<description>From the instructions:  There is chaos in the henhouse &amp;ndash; the clumsy rooster has rolled all the eggs onto the floor of the hayloft, and the hen&amp;rsquo;s nests are empty.  Now al the eggs have to put back into the nests quickly.  If you&amp;rsquo;re lucky the little mouse will help you, but be careful that the rooster doesn&amp;rsquo;t stumble through your nest.&amp;#10;A fun colour and memory game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game contains a large (approx. 40 cm), colourful gameboard illustrated by Hermien Stellmacher.  The board has 20 recessed spaces to hold the wooden eggs (5 each of 4 colours) and 4 matching hen's nests with coloured spaces for each egg.  There is a die showing 1 space of each colour, plus 1 mouse and 1 rooster.  The rules detail 2 versions:&amp;#10;1.  A straight memory version where the aim is to gather the 5 eggs in your colour before the other players.&amp;#10;2.  A version where the winner is the first player to gather 5 eggs in any colour where you keep the egg if you match the colour rolled on the die.  A mouse rolled on the die gives you an extra egg, a rooster returns an egg from your nest to the henhouse floor.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
